WEBVTT

00:10.677 --> 00:12.213
SooMe?

00:13.639 --> 00:15.220
Eric?

00:19.228 --> 00:20.468
PAM:
They're not here.

00:20.979 --> 00:23.061
Sookie is. | feel her fear.

00:23.232 --> 00:26.315
She came here on her own.
It's not our fault you weren't invited.

00:26.485 --> 00:28.350
Maybe she's afraid of you.

00:29.154 --> 00:30.314
Did she say that?

00:30.531 --> 00:32.237
I don't think she wants you anymore.

00:32.741 --> 00:36.325
If you try to keep her from me,
I will kill you.

00:36.662 --> 00:39.404
Get a clue, Bill. I'm not the enemy.

00:39.581 --> 00:42.243
I am older and stronger.

00:42.417 --> 00:44.749
You are no match for me.

00:44.920 --> 00:48.663
This is notjust about your relationship,
you infatuated tween.

00:49.007 --> 00:51.259
There's a bigger picture.

00:51.426 --> 00:52.836
Not for me.

00:55.389 --> 00:56.424
SooMe!

00:56.598 --> 00:58.213
Don't you want the key?

00:58.767 --> 01:00.098
[SCREAMING]

01:03.480 --> 01:08.565
Colloidal silver, in stock and overpriced
at your neighborhood health-food store.

02:41.286 --> 02:42.662
[DOOR RATTLING]

02:50.796 --> 02:52.787
YVETTA:
Rush, quick. I help.

02:52.964 --> 02:55.797
-I thought you were on Eric's team.
-Him?

02:55.967 --> 02:57.673
Big, blond stupid. I hate.

02:57.844 --> 03:00.130
Me too. He's a two-faced snaky
son of a bitch.

03:00.305 --> 03:01.636
Bastard and bitch Pam.

03:01.807 --> 03:05.015
You're preaching to the choir.
Get me out of this hole.

03:06.978 --> 03:08.479
PAM:
You bastard!

03:08.647 --> 03:10.478
[BILL SCREAMING & GRUNTING]

03:11.608 --> 03:12.768
Ah!

03:14.111 --> 03:15.772
[SCREAMING]

03:23.745 --> 03:26.361
SOOKIE: What did she do to you?
-Silver particles in water.

03:26.957 --> 03:28.913
SOOKIE:
Your poor face. Can you see?

03:29.084 --> 03:30.324
No, but I Will heal.

03:30.502 --> 03:32.333
Not until we get it off you.

03:32.504 --> 03:34.836
Secure Pam. We can't let her call Eric.

03:35.006 --> 03:37.258
l secure. I secure, no kidding.

03:38.719 --> 03:40.334
Why did Eric throw me down there?

03:41.680 --> 03:44.012
Answer me! Or I'll spray you.

03:44.516 --> 03:46.928
You were supposed to be
a gift for Edgington.

03:47.102 --> 03:50.014
Now we're all gonna die
because of one freaky little human.

03:50.188 --> 03:52.224
-Good.
BILL: We have to go. Eric may come back.

03:54.609 --> 03:56.941
Don't leave me alone
with this idiot immigrant.

03:57.112 --> 03:59.398
This way, honey. I got you.

03:59.573 --> 04:01.609
Idiot? Ha.

04:01.783 --> 04:05.742
-|n Tallinn, I am a cardiologist.
-Ah!

04:07.164 --> 04:08.700
JESUS:
Unbelievable.

04:09.249 --> 04:11.365
Unbelievable.

04:11.543 --> 04:14.159
I had no idea, man. | neverthought.

04:14.337 --> 04:16.202
Is it always like that?

04:16.381 --> 04:19.373
Took me some fucked-up places
and showed me some crazy shit...

04:19.551 --> 04:21.758
...but not like today.

04:21.928 --> 04:25.671
It was so real.

04:25.849 --> 04:27.680
You know, so alive.

04:27.851 --> 04:29.967
l was telling you things
I didn't know I knew.

04:30.145 --> 04:33.603
I mean, without fasting, without praying,
without any other ritual.

04:33.774 --> 04:36.891
We time-traveled into ourselves.
There were fucking answers there.

04:37.068 --> 04:41.277
Downshift, boyfriend. I'm a V veteran
and I know for a fact the blood can lie.

04:41.448 --> 04:43.860
Did that feel like a lie to you?

04:45.577 --> 04:47.067
No.

04:47.412 --> 04:48.993
Let's do it again.

04:50.123 --> 04:51.988
Just like a virgin.

04:52.167 --> 04:55.204
Oh, come on, baby. Take me back.

04:56.671 --> 04:58.627
I want to see my people.

04:59.090 --> 05:01.081
I wanna hear what they have to say.

05:01.259 --> 05:06.424
| feel like everything that
I need to learn is just one drop away.

05:06.598 --> 05:09.465
Well, boy, you can't control
the destination.

05:10.185 --> 05:15.270
We can end up in hell
or fucking South Dakota.

05:17.943 --> 05:20.104
You don't know what you're doing.

05:20.445 --> 05:22.276
Please?

05:24.449 --> 05:26.656
Don't make me go back alone.

05:30.747 --> 05:31.987
Look--

05:34.876 --> 05:36.958
-What?
-Stop! Stop.

05:37.629 --> 05:39.415
What is it, man?

05:40.006 --> 05:41.667
What just happened?

05:43.176 --> 05:45.963
Nothing. Nothing.

05:46.847 --> 05:52.638
Just sometimes on V
you get a little aftershock.

05:53.937 --> 05:55.552
What'd you see?

05:56.147 --> 05:57.398
Nothing.

05:58.650 --> 06:00.811
Oh, you saw something.

06:01.319 --> 06:04.857
No, just a head rush of the wrong kind.

06:09.536 --> 06:10.571
Okay.

06:13.290 --> 06:14.496
It's okay.

06:17.502 --> 06:20.164
All right, we'll just-- Come on.

06:22.215 --> 06:23.500
We'll go to bed.

06:24.509 --> 06:28.548
All right? It's time for bed. Come on.

06:30.140 --> 06:32.506
You go home. Um--

06:32.684 --> 06:36.768
I need to rest tonight.

06:42.485 --> 06:45.022
-Hlbehave.
-I won't.

06:45.196 --> 06:47.812
Go on. Let La La rest, okay?

06:48.742 --> 06:50.357
You serious?

06:50.535 --> 06:52.241
I'll call you. No big thing.

06:54.539 --> 06:55.870
Good night.

07:01.087 --> 07:03.373
All right, good night.

07:07.218 --> 07:12.212
It's like a werewolf, only a panther?

07:12.390 --> 07:15.348
Yes. A werepanther.

07:16.645 --> 07:18.886
Well, I'm just the same
as | always been.

07:19.230 --> 07:21.972
I told you I had secrets,
and you said you didn't care.

07:22.150 --> 07:25.313
I thought it was shoplifting
or something.

07:25.946 --> 07:28.062
You could've given me a heads-up.

07:28.239 --> 07:30.651
That was the only way
I knew how to explain.

07:31.952 --> 07:33.817
You know, I thought you'd understand.

07:33.995 --> 07:35.405
I thought you'd be a man.

07:35.705 --> 07:37.912
lam a man.

07:38.083 --> 07:41.041
l was ready to sign up
for a meth dealer's daughter.

07:41.836 --> 07:43.497
Okay.

07:44.214 --> 07:46.546
-I know what you think of me now.
-I didn't mean--

07:46.716 --> 07:49.253
No, just keep blaming me
for things that ain't my fault.

07:49.427 --> 07:52.043
Crystal, my brains feel
like scrambled eggs.

07:52.222 --> 07:55.134
I got my ass chewed by a vampire,
my sister's missing--

07:55.308 --> 07:56.593
Oh, poor you!

07:56.768 --> 08:01.853
All I gotta do is marry my half-brother
and let him breed me till I'm old or dead.

08:08.238 --> 08:10.945
I gotta go look for Sookie.

08:12.283 --> 08:13.534
Wait.

08:16.287 --> 08:18.778
I ain't done talking to you!

08:24.838 --> 08:26.954
-Hey.
-Hey.

08:28.717 --> 08:32.209
Why do | feel like I got muscles
where I've never had muscles?

08:32.387 --> 08:35.049
-|t's the blood.
-|t's you.

08:36.808 --> 08:38.764
Maybe a little.

08:40.645 --> 08:42.431
When we broke up...

08:43.148 --> 08:46.311
...I felt like someone had cut off
my arms and my legs.

08:49.571 --> 08:51.311
I can't do nothing without you.

08:52.198 --> 08:53.984
I missed you so much.

08:54.200 --> 08:55.656
I missed you.

09:04.961 --> 09:06.792
Wait, wait. Hey.

09:06.963 --> 09:09.796
If my arms and legs did get cut off...

09:09.966 --> 09:12.332
...and I drank your blood...

09:12.510 --> 09:14.091
...would they grow back?

09:15.180 --> 09:17.091
We got more important things
to discuss.

09:17.265 --> 09:19.005
I love you.

09:19.476 --> 09:20.511
I love you.

09:21.436 --> 09:23.142
That's all that's important to me.

09:25.857 --> 09:28.189
-You save me.
-Yeah, but you don't know.

09:28.359 --> 09:31.692
Don't know, don't care. Kiss me.

09:35.450 --> 09:37.441
I killed a trucker.

09:46.419 --> 09:47.875
I'm sure that you had to.

09:48.797 --> 09:50.708
I didn't.

09:53.051 --> 09:54.257
It was an accident.

09:55.011 --> 09:56.046
How?

09:56.221 --> 09:57.711
It was after we broke up...

09:58.306 --> 10:00.388
...and I got too hungry
and drained him dead.

10:00.558 --> 10:03.095
But that was before I learned
how to do it right.

10:07.398 --> 10:09.354
This is what you think you love.

10:09.526 --> 10:11.983
This is what I really am.

10:12.153 --> 10:14.439
I tried, but I can't live on Tru Blood.

10:14.614 --> 10:18.402
| drink human blood,
and I'm not gonna stop.

10:26.918 --> 10:28.704
Drink me.

10:58.950 --> 11:00.406
[HOYT GRUNTS]

11:17.135 --> 11:19.797
Talbot adores this one.

11:20.471 --> 11:22.007
Adored.

11:22.891 --> 11:27.305
I'm having trouble switching tenses.
You understand.

11:29.939 --> 11:31.895
Why did you do it?

11:32.775 --> 11:34.151
Talbot never harmed you.

11:34.319 --> 11:36.856
ERIC:
You loved him more than anyone.

11:37.030 --> 11:39.021
So he had to die.

11:39.490 --> 11:42.152
RUSSELL: I'm about to put an end
to your insignificant existence.

11:42.327 --> 11:45.364
This is not the time to be obscure.

11:48.875 --> 11:54.495
A thousand years ago, you brought
your wolves among the Vikings...

11:55.423 --> 11:58.290
...to butcher a human family.

12:01.471 --> 12:02.677
My family.

12:03.473 --> 12:05.464
Apparently, you wanted
my father's crown...

12:05.642 --> 12:07.928
...for your vast collection
of meaningless shit.

12:09.312 --> 12:12.395
[LAUGHING]

12:14.442 --> 12:16.683
My, my.

12:17.779 --> 12:21.317
To lose the one man I ever loved because
you miss your mommy and daddy?

12:21.491 --> 12:23.527
Well, that is a kick in the pants.

12:23.701 --> 12:27.740
There are consequences,
even for Russell Edgington.

12:27.914 --> 12:29.620
Life is absurd.

12:29.791 --> 12:32.123
[LAUGHS]

12:32.794 --> 12:34.204
Still...

12:34.712 --> 12:36.418
...l'm excited to destroy you.

12:36.589 --> 12:39.205
My loved ones are dead,
now Talbot is dead. We're even.

12:39.384 --> 12:41.966
Don't beg for mercy. It's such a bore.

12:42.136 --> 12:45.879
I couldn't help but notice
your expanding ambitions.

12:46.224 --> 12:49.216
You're after the whole world now,
aren't you?

12:50.395 --> 12:51.805
Well, I can help you get it.

12:51.980 --> 12:57.771
Eric, you are nothing more than
a lump of muscle with a blood grudge.

12:57.944 --> 12:59.400
You got lucky.

12:59.570 --> 13:03.529
You couldn't possibly comprehend
what I'm after.

13:03.866 --> 13:05.652
We should begin.

13:10.081 --> 13:12.197
I can offer you the sun.

13:12.834 --> 13:16.702
Oh, daywalking? Oh, the old myth.

13:16.879 --> 13:19.211
That was around when l was turned.
You're pathetic.

13:19.382 --> 13:21.168
It's not a myth, not at all.

13:25.596 --> 13:27.052
Go on.

13:27.682 --> 13:29.013
Spin your little fairy tale.

13:29.183 --> 13:31.765
I will show you how to do it.

13:32.478 --> 13:34.059
Now tell me you don't want it.

13:34.230 --> 13:36.687
I never said I didn't want it.

13:37.400 --> 13:41.564
It's the ultimate vampire dream, isn't it?

13:41.863 --> 13:44.149
No one could stand against me.

13:44.615 --> 13:48.449
You would be invulnerable.

13:49.454 --> 13:51.319
If I'm wrong...

13:54.375 --> 13:56.331
...kill me tomorrow.

14:02.467 --> 14:05.254
[RUSSELL LAUGHING]

14:06.304 --> 14:08.386
Clever boy.

14:09.432 --> 14:10.888
To tempt me.

14:12.435 --> 14:15.927
[UPBEAT PHONE RINGTONE PLAYING]

14:20.651 --> 14:21.857
Not a good time.

14:22.028 --> 14:28.149
No shit. Bill and Sookie escaped
and Yvetta cleaned out the cash. Ow!

14:28.326 --> 14:32.911
I'm so sorry.
It was dug in there real good.

14:33.081 --> 14:35.572
Can I get you something
to make you feel better?

14:35.750 --> 14:38.537
-I need a drink.
-Ah!

14:51.182 --> 14:53.673
-Why did you go to Eric?
-I had to ask him a question.

14:54.310 --> 14:55.766
What question?

14:56.687 --> 14:58.348
It doesn't matter.

15:01.025 --> 15:03.357
Look what he did to you.

15:05.196 --> 15:09.109
He's betrayed you, used you,
drawn you into danger.

15:11.160 --> 15:14.368
I've made mistakes trying to
keep you safe, but I'm nothing like Eric.

15:14.539 --> 15:15.619
Of course you're not.

15:16.958 --> 15:21.247
I love you, Bill,
but after this whole Mississippi mess...

15:21.421 --> 15:23.707
...l'd be a crazy woman
to trust either of you.

15:25.758 --> 15:26.998
You have feelings for him?

15:27.885 --> 15:30.137
Not "feelings" feelings.

15:32.140 --> 15:33.926
I drank his blood. I can't help it.

15:34.475 --> 15:35.555
It's more than that.

15:36.185 --> 15:39.393
You weren't there on that roof
with Godric.

15:39.564 --> 15:43.807
I saw a whole other side to him,
and it was real.

15:47.155 --> 15:51.319
When this is over, let's begin again.

15:51.742 --> 15:52.822
We'll be new.

15:53.953 --> 15:55.693
Will we?

15:56.289 --> 15:57.574
I don't know.

15:57.748 --> 16:00.160
I don't know if people change,
even when they try.

16:00.710 --> 16:02.746
We can if we want to.

16:06.174 --> 16:07.584
Do you want to?

16:08.092 --> 16:10.128
You know I do.

16:37.205 --> 16:39.947
[CRYING]

16:46.422 --> 16:48.708
There's no 100 percent guarantee
it's gonna work.

16:48.883 --> 16:51.625
-You said that.
-And you can always change your mind.

16:52.470 --> 16:54.256
Are you trying to talk me out of it?

16:54.430 --> 16:57.046
You need to know the truth,
and I want you to be sure.

16:57.225 --> 16:59.466
I'm sure, I'm sure.

17:02.647 --> 17:04.183
I just want to get it over with.

17:04.941 --> 17:06.181
Okay.

17:07.527 --> 17:09.483
After work, okay?

17:17.328 --> 17:19.819
-Moron! Get the hell out of my way.
-Sorry.

17:19.997 --> 17:21.077
SAM:
What you looking at?

17:21.249 --> 17:23.160
Mind your own goddamn business!

17:23.334 --> 17:24.824
Jesus Christ, you're ugly!

17:25.670 --> 17:27.410
WOMAN 1: Well, that's just rude.
ARLENE: Hey!

17:28.130 --> 17:29.415
You ain't paid your check.

17:29.590 --> 17:33.082
Where's my whiskey?
Keep a bottle back here...

17:33.261 --> 17:36.344
...special for me, and all y'all know it!

17:36.514 --> 17:38.846
Give me back my fucking whiskey!

17:39.350 --> 17:41.466
WOMAN 2:
What is his problem?

17:42.478 --> 17:44.184
Let's take it easy, Sam.

17:44.355 --> 17:45.765
Kiss my ass!

17:45.940 --> 17:49.558
Okay. Well, you're hurting. I can tell.

17:49.735 --> 17:52.522
-Let's go and talk about it.
-Who do you think you are?

17:53.114 --> 17:55.070
-I'm your friend.
-I'm your boss.

17:56.367 --> 17:58.528
This is the liquor talking, Sam.
It ain't you.

17:58.703 --> 18:00.318
No, it is me.

18:00.496 --> 18:03.909
All right, get back in the kitchen,
you shell-shocked motherfucker.

18:04.083 --> 18:05.243
[ARLENE GASPS]

18:05.418 --> 18:06.999
Sam Merlotte.

18:07.169 --> 18:09.751
You're gonna hate yourself
for saying that.

18:13.050 --> 18:15.962
-You apologize to Terry right now.
-No.

18:16.137 --> 18:18.048
How could you be so hateful and mean?

18:18.222 --> 18:21.840
He breaks his back for you.
He looks up to you. He loves you.

18:22.018 --> 18:23.554
That ain't my problem.

18:23.728 --> 18:25.514
Look, I get that you're in a mood...

18:25.688 --> 18:29.101
...but you're polluting our positive vibes,
and it's killing our tips.

18:29.275 --> 18:31.812
Quit scaring the customers off.
Go home and pass out.

18:31.986 --> 18:34.853
Let's get this straight.
I don't take shit from you.

18:35.031 --> 18:37.443
Okay? You work for me.
This is my place.

18:37.617 --> 18:40.575
So you bitches do yourjob
and shut the fuck up.

18:40.745 --> 18:41.780
Sam?

18:41.954 --> 18:44.366
Nobody talks to me that way, okay?

18:44.540 --> 18:46.246
You wait your own goddamn tables.

18:46.584 --> 18:50.076
Come on, Arlene, let's go. Grab the salt.

18:50.588 --> 18:53.295
-Why?
-| forgot to bring mine.

19:00.431 --> 19:02.387
SOOKIE [ON RECORDING]:
Leave a message.

19:02.558 --> 19:04.765
Sookie, where are you?

19:07.897 --> 19:09.853
[INDISTINCTLY DIALOGUE
IN BACKGROUND]

19:10.024 --> 19:11.184
KITCH:
Hut!

19:14.737 --> 19:16.273
Hut!

19:17.490 --> 19:18.855
Hut!

19:19.033 --> 19:22.196
Come on, get this. Hut!

19:25.956 --> 19:27.867
Hut! Run!

19:31.087 --> 19:32.452
Hut!

19:37.927 --> 19:39.167
Hut!

19:40.805 --> 19:42.170
Hut!

19:42.682 --> 19:45.219
Kitch, you said you'd come back
to the house with me...

19:45.393 --> 19:47.008
...and watch me try on outfits.

19:48.104 --> 19:49.685
Go!

19:49.980 --> 19:52.642
-You don't quit now, I'll go without you.
-Go ahead.

19:54.235 --> 19:55.520
Hut!

19:55.695 --> 19:58.061
-Dildo.
-Hut!

19:59.448 --> 20:01.404
Fine. I'll wait for you
in the parking lot.

20:01.575 --> 20:04.362
Hurry up. Let's go.

20:05.663 --> 20:07.153
Hut!

20:08.749 --> 20:10.330
Hut!

20:13.212 --> 20:14.418
Damn. Ugh!

20:15.172 --> 20:16.457
KITCH:
Hut!

20:17.800 --> 20:19.415
Ugh! Argh!

20:19.593 --> 20:21.504
KITCH:
Go deep!

20:26.851 --> 20:28.512
Dude?

20:30.563 --> 20:32.599
KITCH:
Let's go, let's go! Pick it up!

20:32.773 --> 20:34.183
Practice ain't over yet!

20:34.984 --> 20:37.396
Come on. Let's go, let's go.
Pick it up, pick it up!

20:41.157 --> 20:43.239
[KNOCKING]

20:53.502 --> 20:55.584
What are you doing here
at this time of night?

20:56.213 --> 20:59.000
It didn't work, Ms. Fortenberry.

20:59.175 --> 21:00.711
Hoyt doesn't want me.

21:01.051 --> 21:05.090
Oh, darn it all to heck. Dagnabit.

21:05.264 --> 21:09.633
Shitfire. I could wring his big old neck.

21:09.810 --> 21:13.052
How could I bring up a child
so willful and dumb?

21:15.065 --> 21:18.774
I even offered him my virginity,
and he turned me down flat.

21:18.944 --> 21:22.857
Oh, Summer. I appreciate that.

21:23.032 --> 21:25.774
Even if you broke God's law.

21:26.577 --> 21:29.990
It's my fault. I'm not tall like her.

21:30.164 --> 21:33.702
Can't even reach stuff on
my own closet shelf without a grabber.

21:33.876 --> 21:35.332
And I'm not pretty like her.

21:35.503 --> 21:37.585
Oh, don't say such a thing.

21:37.755 --> 21:42.545
She's not even alive,
and you are cute as pigs.

21:42.718 --> 21:46.427
I baked for him.
I opened up my heart to him.

21:46.597 --> 21:49.259
Even showed him my best undenNear.

21:49.433 --> 21:51.264
There's nothing else I could do.

21:51.435 --> 21:53.596
You are not to blame, honey.

21:53.771 --> 21:58.640
That redheaded bloodsucker
put a spell on him.

22:00.653 --> 22:02.484
I'm sorry I failed you.

22:04.532 --> 22:06.614
I'll never get over my Bear.

22:07.201 --> 22:09.157
Oh, don't you dare give up.

22:09.328 --> 22:12.115
We are not finished...

22:12.289 --> 22:15.122
...not by along shot.

22:15.292 --> 22:16.793
Okay.

22:17.670 --> 22:20.207
[COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYING ON SPEAKERS]

22:20.381 --> 22:22.292
SAM:
Who had the fries?

22:29.306 --> 22:32.264
-I could use some help here.
-I can see that.

22:32.434 --> 22:34.641
Too bad I ain't working tonight.

22:34.812 --> 22:35.972
SAM:
Thanks a lot.

22:47.157 --> 22:48.943
Hey, Tara.

22:50.411 --> 22:52.276
Mind if I sit?

22:53.622 --> 22:56.489
Well, no. I guess not.

22:59.336 --> 23:00.997
How you doing?

23:04.383 --> 23:06.669
Looks like Sam had one too many.

23:06.844 --> 23:10.632
I never saw him this way. Heh, heh.

23:17.897 --> 23:21.435
If you're hungry, you can eat my rings.
I didn't touch them.

23:21.609 --> 23:24.191
My stomach ain't what it was,
you know?

23:24.361 --> 23:27.603
I used to drink hot sauce
straight out of the bottle.

23:29.366 --> 23:31.357
That was a good time.

23:40.127 --> 23:42.539
Need a refill. You want anything?

23:42.755 --> 23:44.871
I know about Eggs.

23:47.509 --> 23:49.795
You must think you're pretty slick.

23:49.970 --> 23:52.256
Yeah, you're the shit.

23:52.431 --> 23:56.390
Got your picture in the paper
and a big promotion.

23:56.560 --> 24:00.052
Andy Bellefleur, American hero.

24:01.065 --> 24:03.852
It's all working out so good, right?

24:04.151 --> 24:06.233
But I see what you are.

24:06.528 --> 24:09.144
Liars, murderers.

24:09.865 --> 24:10.980
[COUGHING]

24:11.158 --> 24:13.649
Jason killed him, and you covered it up.

24:13.827 --> 24:16.113
You're a dirty, dirty cop.

24:24.338 --> 24:27.455
-What are you gonna do?
-What can I do?

24:28.342 --> 24:31.334
Nobody cares about Eggs except me.

24:32.388 --> 24:36.882
And I'll miss him for the rest of my life.

24:38.394 --> 24:43.263
But the three of us will always know
he didn't deserve to die.

24:46.944 --> 24:49.936
Well, I don't feel like a hero.

24:55.285 --> 24:59.494
I never wanted nothing like this
to happen.

25:00.249 --> 25:02.456
It was all Maryann.

25:04.128 --> 25:05.493
He was innocent.

25:07.131 --> 25:08.712
God help me.

25:09.466 --> 25:14.631
If I could do it again, if I could go back
and just get ahold of Jason's gun...

25:14.805 --> 25:19.799
...if Eggs had put the knife down,
but he was bound and determined to die.

25:19.977 --> 25:23.140
I couldn't stop him. Jason didn't know.

25:27.985 --> 25:29.816
I'm sorry.

25:33.907 --> 25:36.159
Tara, I'm so sorry.

25:53.594 --> 25:54.834
Take some orders.

25:55.345 --> 25:58.178
TOMMY: I ain't the waitress.
-You are now.

25:59.183 --> 26:01.674
Yeah, well, I don't need this.
I'll remember it.

26:01.852 --> 26:05.436
The hell you will.
The kitchen needs a goddamn ticket.

26:05.606 --> 26:07.562
Do what I tell you and do it right.

26:08.192 --> 26:09.682
-Fuck that!
-Pick it up!

26:09.860 --> 26:11.896
You pick it up! Look at yourself.

26:12.196 --> 26:13.231
Drunk and yelling.

26:13.405 --> 26:16.192
-You're nothing but Joe Lee in a Sam suit.
-Ungrateful punk.

26:16.366 --> 26:19.358
All I've done is help you,
all you've done is been a whiny bitch!

26:20.037 --> 26:21.698
I'm through with you! You're fired!

26:22.122 --> 26:24.534
Pack up your shit.
Get the fuck out of my rental.

26:25.000 --> 26:26.536
Wait.

26:27.461 --> 26:30.874
I lost my temper. It's nothing. I'm sorry.

26:31.048 --> 26:34.040
See? See? I ain't mad anymore.

26:34.218 --> 26:35.253
Did you not hear me?

26:35.427 --> 26:37.213
You're my brother, Sam. You said you--

26:37.387 --> 26:39.764
I'm sick of you. All right? It's over now.

26:39.932 --> 26:42.423
You're the only one I know.
Where am I supposed to go?

26:42.601 --> 26:43.761
Ugh!

26:46.438 --> 26:48.178
I don't care.

26:50.609 --> 26:52.565
All of you, get out of here!

26:53.570 --> 26:55.401
I want this place empty in two minutes.

26:56.240 --> 26:58.572
Merlotte's is fucking closed, goddamn it.

26:58.742 --> 27:02.655
I don't want your fucking money.
I want you gone. Now.

27:02.871 --> 27:05.533
MAN: Come on, sweetheart.
WOMAN: I'm gonna grab my purse.

27:08.210 --> 27:09.700
I said, go away.

27:10.754 --> 27:11.789
No.

27:18.762 --> 27:22.550
I tell you what,
that dungeon this time did me in.

27:22.766 --> 27:25.098
Well, if you'd stayed put
as I asked you to....

27:25.269 --> 27:27.635
I know. But I was
sitting there in the dark...

27:27.813 --> 27:31.397
...and I thought,
"I am done with this shit."

27:31.567 --> 27:35.810
That's why we need a fresh start.
We'll be free of it, I promise you.

27:37.197 --> 27:39.279
What would that be like?

27:39.449 --> 27:41.440
Who would we be if we were normal?

27:42.077 --> 27:44.113
It's hard to even picture it.

27:45.080 --> 27:47.321
Would we live in Gran's house
oryourhouse?

27:47.499 --> 27:50.662
Both. We'd be married, happily married.

27:50.836 --> 27:52.622
And I'm not a waitress anymore.

27:54.298 --> 27:55.583
I'm going to college.

27:55.757 --> 27:58.339
No, I'm a real-estate agent,
and I'm really rich.

27:59.428 --> 28:02.636
I teach third grade and I love myjob.

28:03.557 --> 28:05.969
We'll have a big flower garden.

28:06.268 --> 28:07.348
We grow vegetables.

28:07.519 --> 28:09.134
Tara comes over for dinner...

28:09.313 --> 28:12.055
...and sometimes we double-date
with Arlene and Terry.

28:12.232 --> 28:13.642
And I go fishing with Jason.

28:14.735 --> 28:16.646
We don't even know Eric Northman.

28:18.405 --> 28:20.145
Everything is peaceful.

28:22.451 --> 28:23.440
[SCREAMING]

28:23.619 --> 28:25.530
[TIRES SCREECHING]

28:37.174 --> 28:41.838
HOLLY: We cast the circle with candles,
flame of the spirit.

28:42.012 --> 28:48.224
We draw the circle with salt
for protection and purity.

28:52.481 --> 28:54.267
Amen.

29:02.991 --> 29:06.324
Great Mother, we invoke you.

29:06.495 --> 29:09.077
Blessed be.

29:09.248 --> 29:10.988
[ANIMAL YELPING]

29:11.166 --> 29:12.997
[BIRD CAWING]

29:15.837 --> 29:17.793
Okay, she's here.

29:18.840 --> 29:20.216
You feel her?

29:20.384 --> 29:22.841
I feel something.

29:30.852 --> 29:35.186
My mama passed away
a couple years ago.

29:35.857 --> 29:38.894
She didn't approve of me,
but we were....

29:39.069 --> 29:40.605
We were real close.

29:40.779 --> 29:43.065
My mama hated me.

29:43.240 --> 29:46.824
Guess that's what got me looking
for the real thing.

29:46.994 --> 29:48.734
You sure you're totally healthy?

29:49.997 --> 29:53.865
Gyno ran all the tests.
I got the body of a tired teenager.

29:54.042 --> 29:57.034
-That for me?
-Oh, God, no. No, no. These are oils.

29:57.254 --> 30:00.872
You'd fall over dead.
You need a decoction.

30:01.133 --> 30:03.169
A de-what?

30:03.343 --> 30:05.425
It's like herbal tea.

30:05.595 --> 30:10.305
I'll show you how to make it
and when to take it. I wrote it down.

30:10.475 --> 30:12.761
You need to follow
the directions exactly.

30:13.353 --> 30:15.935
-Okay? I mean to the letter.
-I will.

30:17.524 --> 30:21.733
Well, this'll be ready in a little minute.

30:21.903 --> 30:26.772
Some people like to pray before,
you know, help them get focused.

30:26.950 --> 30:29.441
I don't know if God's onboard for this.

30:30.203 --> 30:32.455
Talk to your mother's spirit.

30:33.415 --> 30:35.076
I can't. She'd kill me.

30:35.709 --> 30:37.119
Then talk to the Great Mother.

30:37.794 --> 30:39.625
She's God too.

30:39.796 --> 30:41.787
Oh, just don't step outside the circle.

31:00.817 --> 31:03.934
I never thought of God as a woman...

31:06.656 --> 31:10.524
...but if you're with me tonight,
maybe you are.

31:12.454 --> 31:17.073
And, Mama, if you can hear me,
would you listen?

31:17.667 --> 31:22.127
Really just listen for once?

31:24.132 --> 31:27.295
You gotta know
this is the right thing to do.

31:28.720 --> 31:30.176
It's the only way to be sure...

31:30.347 --> 31:35.683
...that Rene will never pass
his sickness on to the world.

31:36.520 --> 31:38.135
Then...

31:39.147 --> 31:42.810
...Coby and Lisa and Terry
will be safe...

31:42.984 --> 31:46.442
...and I won't have to live
my whole life in fear.

31:46.613 --> 31:50.526
And the baby won't have to be
a crazed killer.

31:51.701 --> 31:54.078
I don't believe in abortion.

31:54.413 --> 31:57.029
I'm doing what needs to be done.

32:02.003 --> 32:05.666
First time you take it,
needs a drop of blood.

32:06.341 --> 32:07.376
Why is that?

32:07.884 --> 32:11.422
Sacrifice. Nothing's free.

32:23.859 --> 32:25.645
[ARLENE GRUNTS]

32:31.992 --> 32:33.528
But...

32:34.202 --> 32:36.579
...if the spirit is meant to be born...

32:36.746 --> 32:40.284
...it'll be born and there's nothing
we can do about it.

32:40.709 --> 32:43.291
It's in the hands of the Goddess now.

32:43.920 --> 32:45.080
I understand.

32:46.298 --> 32:48.789
Four times a day for up to five days.

32:50.135 --> 32:52.046
-Sip it or shoot it?
-Shoot it.

32:55.682 --> 32:56.717
Ech.

32:59.186 --> 33:02.349
Blessed be.

33:06.943 --> 33:08.899
KITCH:
Tired? Wore out?

33:09.070 --> 33:11.732
Don't give me that shit.
Y'all pussies get back to work.

33:11.907 --> 33:13.272
MAN:
Shut up, man. I'm going home.

33:13.450 --> 33:15.816
KITCH: Yeah, well, I'm gonna run laps.
I'll see you later.

33:15.994 --> 33:17.234
MAN:
Got nothing left, man.

33:17.412 --> 33:20.779
Well, Grandpa Stackhouse.
You come to wish me luck?

33:21.082 --> 33:24.370
You don't need luck, Kitch. You're on V.

33:26.505 --> 33:30.669
I'm not saying I am,
but if I was, so what?

33:32.135 --> 33:34.626
V's a illegal substance.

33:35.263 --> 33:39.472
That makes you a criminal...

33:39.643 --> 33:43.261
...a drug abuser and a cheater.

33:44.022 --> 33:47.139
On top of which, you're already
a cocky bullshit motherfucker.

33:47.317 --> 33:49.103
Is that right?

33:49.611 --> 33:51.101
I'm taking you down, boy.

33:51.279 --> 33:54.066
I'll tell your coach,
your mom and dad, and your principal.

33:54.241 --> 33:55.981
My coach is the one who gave me the V.

33:56.910 --> 33:59.367
-Bullshit.
-My parents are paying for it.

33:59.538 --> 34:02.826
My principal, he uses it for his sex life.

34:03.750 --> 34:06.366
They won't care what you say,
and you can't prove it.

34:06.753 --> 34:08.664
There are no tests that can trace it.

34:09.506 --> 34:11.212
That ain't fair.

34:11.591 --> 34:13.127
I was an athlete out there.

34:14.678 --> 34:17.511
I didn't get help from nothing or nobody
but my team.

34:17.681 --> 34:19.342
That's the way it's supposed to be.

34:19.849 --> 34:22.511
Look at the pros.
Everybody's taking something.

34:23.186 --> 34:25.222
No dope, no glory.

34:25.522 --> 34:28.104
My record stands, asshole.

34:28.275 --> 34:30.641
You're no athlete. You never will be.

34:30.860 --> 34:32.896
Well, that's funny.

34:33.071 --> 34:35.858
See, there's a scout from LSU
coming to the game...

34:36.032 --> 34:38.444
...especially to hand me a scholarship.

34:38.618 --> 34:41.405
I won't have to stay here
and join the chain gang like you.

34:44.624 --> 34:46.239
Kitch!

34:47.085 --> 34:49.542
I'm gonna blow your record
to smithereens. Heh, heh.

34:49.713 --> 34:52.546
-It doesn't count.
-Well, tell that to the newspapers.

34:55.135 --> 34:56.375
Fuck you.

34:57.804 --> 34:59.795
[GIRL GIGGLING]

35:02.392 --> 35:05.134
FEMALE VOICE 1:
Lafayette.

35:05.604 --> 35:08.061
La La.

35:08.231 --> 35:09.607
[LAUGHTER & MONKEY GIBBERING]

35:09.774 --> 35:10.854
FEMALE VOICE 2:
Lafayette.

35:11.067 --> 35:13.228
MALE VOICE 1:
Lafayette.

35:13.403 --> 35:17.237
[CHATTERING]

35:19.618 --> 35:20.778
MALE VOICE 1:
Lafayette.

35:20.952 --> 35:22.567
FEMALE DOLL:
Come with us.

35:23.204 --> 35:25.741
[CHATTERING & MONKEY GIBBERING]

35:26.625 --> 35:28.581
MALE VOICE 2:
We need you.

35:28.752 --> 35:29.912
MALE VOICE 1:
Lafayette.

35:30.086 --> 35:32.873
Lafayette. Lafayette.

35:35.884 --> 35:37.715
[TIRES SCREECH]

35:44.184 --> 35:47.768
RUSSELL: Everything as far as your deficient
human eye can see will be mine.

35:47.937 --> 35:50.269
-Pride goeth before a fall.
RUSSELL: Ha, ha, ha.

35:50.565 --> 35:51.850
ERIC:
Hit me.

35:52.233 --> 35:54.098
RUSSELL: Don't you see, Miss Stackhouse?
-Hit me.

35:54.277 --> 35:58.270
-Your country is begging to be conquered.
-You don't know much about America.

35:59.157 --> 36:02.115
RUSSELL: Graffiti is the desperate cry
of your dying reign.

36:02.285 --> 36:04.867
Your so-called society is disintegrating.

36:05.038 --> 36:06.403
[LAUGHING]

36:08.667 --> 36:13.206
Soon there will be anarchy
and then there will be me.

36:13.380 --> 36:15.792
[BILL & ERIC GRUNTING]

36:18.802 --> 36:20.884
[BOTH GRUNTING]

36:29.145 --> 36:30.646
I have a plan.

36:30.814 --> 36:32.554
Will it save her?

36:33.149 --> 36:35.936
TARA:
What crawled up your butt tonight?

36:36.319 --> 36:37.820
SAM:
Nothing.

36:39.030 --> 36:41.271
Expressing my feelings.

36:42.158 --> 36:43.989
That a problem for you?

36:44.494 --> 36:46.109
TARA:
Nope.

36:47.330 --> 36:48.991
You go off on people all the time.

36:49.165 --> 36:52.828
Cussing, fighting, raising hell.

36:53.002 --> 36:55.163
Feels good, don't it?

36:55.505 --> 36:59.373
But you notice I'm not popular.
Not a lot of friends.

36:59.551 --> 37:02.338
-You think I got a lot of friends?
-Not after tonight.

37:02.512 --> 37:03.627
Even before tonight?

37:04.264 --> 37:07.427
You had Terry before
you jumped all over him.

37:07.600 --> 37:10.558
You had Arlene before
you called her a bitch.

37:10.729 --> 37:13.471
Oh, yeah. I heard about it.

37:14.941 --> 37:17.683
You had Tommy before
you ripped him a new asshole.

37:18.486 --> 37:20.863
Well, it ain't true.

37:21.865 --> 37:23.196
I got nobody.

37:23.950 --> 37:25.531
You got me.

37:28.913 --> 37:30.449
Do I?

37:31.332 --> 37:33.197
I'm here, aren't I?

37:35.420 --> 37:36.705
Nobody knows me.

37:37.464 --> 37:39.045
It's not like you make it easy.

37:41.050 --> 37:45.840
Yeah, people think of Sam, it's like,
"Oh, yeah. Yeah, he's nice.

37:46.014 --> 37:49.427
Yeah, I'll go ask him to do some
inconvenient shitty thing...

37:49.601 --> 37:53.685
...and he'll do it,
because he's such a good guy."

37:53.855 --> 37:58.098
Or, "Yeah, I'll treat Sam like a cowpie.
He won't mind. He's so nice."

37:58.276 --> 38:00.358
[LAUGHING]

38:02.071 --> 38:04.904
Not one person in the world
thinks that about me.

38:06.201 --> 38:07.361
[SAM CHUCKLES]

38:07.744 --> 38:12.613
"Don't invite Tara to the party.
She'll get pissed off and beat the cat."

38:13.124 --> 38:16.867
"Put away the wedding china.
Tara's coming over."

38:18.213 --> 38:20.579
-You know what the secret is?
-What's the secret?

38:21.633 --> 38:23.043
We're not so different.

38:24.052 --> 38:25.883
-No?
-Uh-uh.

38:26.429 --> 38:29.637
-We're not nice.
-We're not nice at all.

38:29.808 --> 38:31.139
SAM:
Uh-uh.

38:31.351 --> 38:34.718
You feel like dropping by
my nasty-ass trailer?

38:34.938 --> 38:36.098
TARA: Yeah.
-Yeah?

38:36.272 --> 38:37.978
TARA:
Let's fuck.

38:44.239 --> 38:47.231
[BOTH GRUNTING]

39:20.650 --> 39:24.643
WOMAN:
Arlene? Where you at?

39:26.489 --> 39:27.695
Arlene?

39:27.866 --> 39:31.654
Hey, Mama. I'm right here.

39:31.828 --> 39:33.944
WOMAN:
Put up that fishing pole and come home.

39:34.122 --> 39:35.487
We're waiting on you.

39:36.374 --> 39:37.910
In a little while.

39:38.084 --> 39:41.702
WOMAN: Arlene? Arlene?
TERRY: Arlene?

39:44.173 --> 39:45.549
Arlene?

39:46.009 --> 39:49.217
Arlene? Jesus God, please wake up.

39:49.846 --> 39:51.507
Can you hear me?

39:53.141 --> 39:55.348
Of course I can hear you.
One of the kids sick?

39:57.270 --> 39:59.181
Oh, my God.

40:01.649 --> 40:04.026
-Oh, my God.
-I'm calling 911.

40:04.193 --> 40:05.694
No, wait.

40:10.158 --> 40:12.865
Oh, you don't have to do that.
I'm okay. I can tell.

40:14.871 --> 40:17.738
I'll get cleaned up, and you can
take me to the hospital.

40:17.916 --> 40:20.908
Can you bring me that box of pads
under the bathroom sink?

40:21.085 --> 40:24.327
-It looks like you're dying.
-I'm not.

40:24.505 --> 40:27.918
But I'm sorry, honey.
I think we're losing the baby.

40:28.134 --> 40:32.093
-Don't tell me that. No, no, no.
-Shh, shh.

40:32.472 --> 40:34.428
TERRY: No, no.
-Shh, shh, shh.

40:34.599 --> 40:37.807
Better hurry, now. We'll cry later, okay?

40:37.977 --> 40:39.558
Okay?

40:45.193 --> 40:46.683
[SIGHS]

40:55.995 --> 40:57.405
CRYSTAL:
Did you find her?

40:59.832 --> 41:03.745
No. And I don't know where else to look
or what else to do.

41:03.920 --> 41:05.410
Some fucking cop I am.

41:07.632 --> 41:09.588
-I was gonna go.
-I don't wanna break up.

41:10.385 --> 41:11.500
Don't play with me.

41:11.678 --> 41:13.634
I'm not playing. I mean it.

41:15.098 --> 41:17.464
No one in this town
is what they're supposed to be.

41:17.642 --> 41:20.759
So you turn into a panther.
What the hell? That ain't so bad.

41:22.438 --> 41:24.815
Besides, I love you.

41:35.034 --> 41:37.696
-You love a girl from Hotshot.
-Not anymore. You ran away.

41:37.870 --> 41:40.703
I tried, but I'm going back,
and I want you to come with me.

41:41.124 --> 41:43.456
-We gotta stop that raid.
-Why?

41:43.626 --> 41:45.127
Because all those innocent kids.

41:45.294 --> 41:46.704
I saw a boy there once...

41:46.879 --> 41:49.791
...he was making awful noises
and chewing on something dead.

41:49.966 --> 41:53.504
That's my double cousin Bufort.
He ain't right, but he never hurt nobody.

41:53.678 --> 41:55.839
We can't go against the DE-fucking-A.

41:56.014 --> 41:57.424
We don't got no choice.

41:57.974 --> 42:00.590
Felton and Daddy are crazy.
I've heard them say it.

42:00.768 --> 42:03.635
They will light that whole place on fire
and everybody in it.

42:03.813 --> 42:06.099
It'll be Waco all over again.

42:06.649 --> 42:07.809
I'm going.

42:08.484 --> 42:10.349
With or without you.

42:12.864 --> 42:14.274
RUSSELL:
Fairies?

42:14.449 --> 42:15.985
[RUSSELL CHUCKLES]

42:16.159 --> 42:19.868
You seriously expect me
to believe she's fairy?

42:20.329 --> 42:25.744
A species extinct for millennia?
If they ever existed at all.

42:26.169 --> 42:29.536
You think I wouldn't notice
if there were fairies bouncing around?

42:29.714 --> 42:31.170
ERIC:
I didn't say she was full fairy.

42:31.507 --> 42:33.998
She's a human-fairy hybrid...

42:34.177 --> 42:36.168
...which helps save her from detection.

42:37.847 --> 42:41.339
She may well be the last of her kind...

42:41.559 --> 42:43.971
...your only chance to walk in the sun.

42:45.063 --> 42:47.930
RUSSELL:
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

42:48.399 --> 42:51.562
Drink her blood. You'll see.

42:51.736 --> 42:53.146
SOOKIE:
Now, that's just nuts.

42:53.321 --> 42:56.028
Nothing in my blood
is a supernatural sunscreen for y'all.

42:56.199 --> 42:57.359
Why would you think that?

43:00.036 --> 43:01.071
Sookie, you're wrong.

43:02.038 --> 43:03.869
-What Eric says is true.
-No.

43:04.540 --> 43:05.746
I never told you.

43:05.917 --> 43:07.657
Bill's experienced it for himself.

43:07.835 --> 43:09.496
Oh, well, that's reassuring.

43:09.670 --> 43:12.332
A testimonial from the mendacious
Mr. Compton.

43:12.507 --> 43:14.919
A new beginning? We'll start over?

43:19.388 --> 43:21.049
Why are you doing this to me?

43:21.224 --> 43:24.216
We've tried fighting him.
We'll never win.

43:24.519 --> 43:27.727
If he develops a taste for your blood,
he may let you live.

43:27.897 --> 43:29.933
-Bil|, please.
-So?

43:30.108 --> 43:32.565
-I'm intrigued.
-Excellent.

43:32.735 --> 43:35.226
I hate you. I hate you all.

43:35.404 --> 43:37.315
-On one condition.
-Whatever you like.

43:37.865 --> 43:39.571
You go first.

43:43.079 --> 43:44.615
I'd love to.

43:45.373 --> 43:47.739
Please stop worrying.

43:48.459 --> 43:50.120
Hey.

43:50.294 --> 43:55.288
It's just God's way of telling us
this child wasn't meant to be.

43:55.591 --> 43:58.003
Didn't you read that
in some of your books?

43:58.177 --> 44:00.008
Yeah. Yeah, I did.

44:00.179 --> 44:02.420
But I never thought
it would happen to us.

44:02.807 --> 44:05.298
I know. It happens to a lot of people.

44:06.018 --> 44:09.101
You shouldn't have been working.
I should've been doing everything.

44:09.272 --> 44:10.853
Shh.

44:11.399 --> 44:13.936
Life goes the way it goes, okay?

44:14.110 --> 44:17.944
We just have to accept it and move on.

44:18.614 --> 44:21.606
Oh, honey. Don't cry.

44:23.119 --> 44:24.404
The results are back.

44:24.579 --> 44:27.116
Doctor, please tell my guy
everything's gonna be okay.

44:27.290 --> 44:30.282
-Yeah, it's gonna be okay.
TERRY: Thank the Lord.

44:30.793 --> 44:33.785
Arlene, you may need to spend
a few days in bed.

44:33.963 --> 44:35.123
Whatever you say, doc.

44:35.298 --> 44:37.880
I'll make sure she does.
I don't wanna lose her too.

44:38.050 --> 44:39.961
Oh, you haven't lost anything.

44:40.136 --> 44:41.626
Baby's still onboard.

44:41.804 --> 44:43.510
What?

44:43.931 --> 44:45.091
[DOCTOR CHUCKLES]

44:45.266 --> 44:47.848
You got a strong little critter in there.

44:48.019 --> 44:49.350
TERRY:
Yeah!

44:50.313 --> 44:51.974
DOCTOR:
Congratulations.

45:04.452 --> 45:08.161
RUSSELL: Now, what other fairy secrets
are you keeping, Miss Stackhouse?

45:08.331 --> 45:11.038
Do you have wings? Do you...?

45:11.209 --> 45:12.995
Don't do it. What if it doesn't work?

45:13.211 --> 45:15.167
Oh, it'll work.

45:17.673 --> 45:18.833
Come on. What's this?

45:19.717 --> 45:22.504
Nothing. It's the bleeds.

45:24.347 --> 45:28.010
You know I love you more
when you're cold and heartless.

45:43.616 --> 45:44.947
Shall we?

45:45.117 --> 45:46.448
Do, let's.

45:46.619 --> 45:48.359
One caveat, gentlemen.

45:48.537 --> 45:52.780
If you drain her completely, that's
the last fairy blood you'll ever drink.

45:53.292 --> 45:55.453
-Good point.
RUSSELL: We are schooled.

45:55.628 --> 45:57.710
Onward to adventure.

45:58.089 --> 46:02.298
If this is you trying to help me,
thanks for nothing.

46:15.398 --> 46:17.229
Oh, for God's sake.

46:18.985 --> 46:20.771
[SCREAMS]

46:25.283 --> 46:26.318
[SOOKIE SCREAMS]

46:26.784 --> 46:28.285
[SCREAMS]

46:30.162 --> 46:31.493
[SCREAMS]

47:30.890 --> 47:33.302
Unchain me. I have to feed Sookie.

47:33.476 --> 47:35.182
It's fairies.

47:35.353 --> 47:38.811
Fucking fairies. Who knew?

47:51.160 --> 47:52.821
[IN FOREIGN DIALOGUE]
Don't let them see.

47:54.622 --> 47:57.534
Let me go or she'll die.

47:57.833 --> 48:00.040
My hands are shaking.

48:01.629 --> 48:03.995
I feel like a little child.

48:08.803 --> 48:12.341
Thousands of years of night.

48:13.766 --> 48:15.757
You can't know.

48:16.685 --> 48:18.266
What are you waiting for?

48:25.069 --> 48:28.482
I have to feed Sookie.
She needs my blood now!

48:29.407 --> 48:31.398
Pam, let me go!

48:42.503 --> 48:43.663
Oh....

48:43.879 --> 48:45.870
It's glorious.

48:46.048 --> 48:47.549
It's sublime.

48:59.895 --> 49:02.352
Silver. You traitor.

49:02.523 --> 49:03.888
Fucking madman!

49:08.154 --> 49:09.815
Be brave.

49:10.531 --> 49:12.522
We'll die together.

49:12.700 --> 49:13.940
[RUSSELL GRUNTING]

49:14.118 --> 49:15.858
[RUSSELL SCREAMING]
